-- A closure created outside a row-polymorphic boundary cannot pin its effects
-- onto the bound row: the body of `\(g) -> g(1)` performs `amb`'s instantiation,
-- and checking it against `forall e0. ... -> Int ! {| e0}` would have to solve
-- that outer row to the rigid `e0`, letting the skolem outlive its binder. The
-- solver rejects the capture with a pointed error instead of leaking it.
fn call_poly(h : forall e0. ((Int) -> Int ! {| amb}) -> Int ! {| e0}, f) = h(f)

fn main() = println(call_poly(\(g) -> g(1), \(x) -> x + 41))
